ZH: 他對公司表現得非常忠心。
EN: He is very loyal to the company.

ZH: 她一直忠心地守護家庭。
EN: She has always been loyal in protecting her family.

ZH: 我們應該對我們的朋友忠心。
EN: We should be loyal to our friends.

ZH: 忠心的僕人被主人寵幸。
EN: The loyal servant is favored by his master.

ZH: 他向國家表現出極度忠心。
EN: He shows extreme loyalty to the country.

ZH: 這個士兵對他的上級非常忠心。
EN: This soldier is very loyal to his superiors.

ZH: 忠心的狗不會離開主人。
EN: A loyal dog will not leave its owner.

ZH: 她是一位忠心的忠實支持者。
EN: She is a loyal and faithful supporter.

ZH: 忠心的管家被家族信任。
EN: The loyal steward is trusted by the family.

ZH: 他給予公司無比的忠心與貢獻。
EN: He has given the company unparalleled loyalty and contribution.

ZH: 忠心不只是言語的承諾，更是行動的表現。
EN: Loyalty is not just a promise in words, but also an expression in actions.

ZH: 做事要誠實忠心。
EN: Do things with honesty and loyalty.

ZH: 忠心是建立信任的基石。
EN: Loyalty is the cornerstone of trust.

ZH: 忠心的受雇員工受到公司的尊重。
EN: The loyal employee is respected by the company.

ZH: 忠心的職員往往受到更多的機會。
EN: Loyal staff members often receive more opportunities.

ZH: 公司需要忠心的員工團隊。
EN: Companies need a loyal team of employees.

ZH: 战友之间必须保持忠心。
EN: Loyalty must be maintained among comrades.

ZH: 忠心是建立良好關係的基石。
EN: Loyalty is the foundation of building good relationships.

ZH: 忠心幫助我們克服困難。
EN: Loyalty helps us overcome difficulties.

ZH: 忠心關係長跑贏得對方的信任。
EN: Loyal relationships win the trust of the other party in the long run.
